**.NET Core Version:**
All Versions from NetFx2.0 to CoreFx5.0

**Have you experienced this same bug with .NET Framework?**
Yes

**Problem description:**
Assigning a TreeNode object to the TreeNodeCollection Index property inserts it to the underlying Windows TreeView control rather than updating the existing, and causes the .NET Nodes collection no longer to be in sync with the Windows TreeView control.


**Expected behavior:**
Node should be updated.

**Minimal repro:**
* Create a new WinForms App
* Insert a TreeView on the Form.
* Insert the folloing code in the Form_Load event handler.

```
       private void Form1_Load(object sender, EventArgs e)
        {
            treeView1.Nodes.Clear();

            treeView1.Nodes.Add(new TreeNode("Item1"));
            treeView1.Nodes.Add(new TreeNode("Item2_node"));
            treeView1.Nodes.Add(new TreeNode("Item3"));
  
            var node = treeView1.Nodes[1];
            treeView1.Nodes[1] = node;
        }
```  
